16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Transportation
19 22–218.
20 (c) (1) A person may not drive or move on any highway any vehicle or
21 equipment that is equipped with or displays any light or signal device designed to emit an
22 oscillating, rotating, blinking, or other type of emission of light, unless designated and
23 authorized by the Administrator as indicated in paragraphs (2) through (13) of this
24 subsection. The provisions of this section do not prohibit the display and use of any lighting
25 device that may be permitted or required elsewhere in the Maryland Vehicle Law.
